properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Snow, rain, and strong winds expected. Total snowfall: 2 to 4 cm tonight, except 10 cm inland and over higher terrain. Additional 2 to 4 cm Tuesday night. Total rainfall: 15 to 25 mm. Maximum wind gusts: southeasterly 70 to 80 km/h on Tuesday becoming northwesterly 80 to 90 km/h Tuesday night, with higher coastal gusts possible. Locations: southeastern Labrador. Remarks: Snow, freezing rain, or ice pellets will change to rain overnight tonight. The rain will change back to snow late Tuesday afternoon or evening before ending later Tuesday night. This snow will combine with strong northwesterly winds to reduce visibility at times in blowing snow, especially over exposed areas. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. properties.Title: Storm Surge Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Higher than normal water levels with large waves are expected near the coast. Warning of potential breaking sea conditions and overwash issued jointly by Fisheries and Oceans Canada (Science) and the Meteorological Service of Canada - Quebec Region on 2020-11-24. Higher than normal water levels and large waves are expected near the coast during the period in question. An intense low pressure system approaching from New England will give high winds over the areas listed below. The combination of these winds and the current run of medium-amplitude tidal ranges may produce minor breaking sea conditions along the coast near the following localities on the dates and at the times specified (Eastern Standard Time). Rimouski - Mont-Joli: 2020-11-24, from 08:00 AM to 12:00 PM. Matane: 2020-11-24, from 08:00 AM to 12:00 PM. Sainte-Anne-des-Monts - Grande-Vallée: 2020-11-24, from 08:00 AM to 12:00 PM. Chevery: 2020-11-24, from 04:00 AM to 08:00 AM. Blanc-Sablon: 2020-11-24, from 04:00 AM to 08:00 AM. ### Storm surge warnings are issued when water levels pose a threat to coastal regions.
